	   <tr><td colspan=2>He's talking about simply using the buff as a dispell protection in your first couple buff spots, thats all. Its actually good to have like 2-3 insta click items, you can click them all on, then get all your buffs, then as long as you don't have a bard, just click the 3rd instaclick one off. That way if you get dispelled it just takes your instaclicks, and if the mob lands a magic spell, you can just click off the instaclick buffs, cancel magic yourself and not have to cancel magic all your good buffs first.<br>Then click all the instaclicks back on, and you're good as new =]<br><br>Of course this is bothersome as the 2-3 clickable items do bring you closer to your 15 buff limit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of course the situation where this is most useful is raid situations, ie the one where you are most likely to be at the 15 buff limit.  But VI is working to increase that limit with the release of PoP upcoming, and if they do, it will become much more effective.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Oct  7 08:05:21 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>(Current char I'm focusing on...)<br>Ultenth<br>24th Season Iksar Shaman of the Scaled Mystics<br>(Innoruuk)<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=393040" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=393040</a></td></tr>
